<div id="content" lang="en" dir="ltr">
<h2 id="head-7fd26d925c53fa0c24d939a72316643bb34384d1">Zombie corruptions</h2>
<h3 id="head-26546bea6e8e2b7d6ac5191f825bffec4c12021e">Still blood</h3>
Shadow of death makes your blood circulate hardly at all. This makes thinking and reacting harder, but slows your digestion: -1 to int, -1 to dex. <h3 id="head-38b10adde1819f51de2f391a2e957cdd4587f174">Cold blood</h3>
Your body temperature is the same as that of your  surroundings. This makes movement slower, but makes you tougher: -clvl/10 to speed, -1 to dex, +2 to con, +3 to hit die (reroll  life), -2 chr <h3 id="head-ec04063d1e2568e4cfa6b79092937f75c9f0ab7b">Stale blood</h3>
Your body is decaying. This makes you skin rot  and peel off, weakenes your muscles and greatly readuces your  intellect. This condition is not healthy. -5 to int, -6 to  wis, -3 to str, -3 to con, -5 speed, -5 chr, hp drain, black  breath. When you die in this condition you are resurrected,  but gain the last corruption, making you a full blown zombie. <h3 id="head-592258c236752e79894ccc0a9132547d02ba6305">Dead blood</h3>
You have died and returned as a zombie. The nether  forces that sustain your unlife fill your dead muscles with  unnatural strength and accuracy, and since you don't depend  much on your body's condition it takes a lot to hurt you.  +5+clvl/10 to speed, +4 to con, +6 to str, +5 to con <hr size="3">
 <a href="./amaurea">amaurea</a>: We need a set of corruptions most of the subraces. I have tried to come up with a set for zombies, but it is not complete. I think Cold blood needs to be replaced, and we should have two corruptions before Stale blood, I think. <p>
<a href="./NerdanelVampire">NerdanelVampire</a>: I took the liberty of editing in the Still blood corruption. The idea is somewhat based on Necromancy in Naat by <a href="./Clark_20Ashton_20Smith">Clark Ashton Smith</a> and what happens to Yadar. 
</p>
